node.text: I’m going to disappear from IG for a bit. I always told myself I wouldn’t let this thing become a distraction but it has in some ways. Thank you all for the enormous amounts of inspiration and support. Take care, everyone!

August
-
I’m partnering with @booooooom to offer this 11” x 14” time-limited edition print, exclusively on their online shop. The edition size will be limited by the number of prints sold between now and December 3rd and it will never be re-printed. 20% of sales (edit: I’ve decided to donate all of my profits) will be donated to the California Wildfire Relief efforts via @calfund. Link in bio.

Slow Reveal, 2018
Available in editions of 52x68” and 34x44” (DM for details)

South 1, Texas
-
Editioned at 50 x 62” / 38 x 46” / 28 x 34” and available to purchase on @artsy (link in bio).

Rift
-
Thank you to @rosalina_la_contessa for featuring work from my recent exhibition on the Beautiful Things blog. You can check it out at bit.ly/2NGh67a

West 3, California, 2016
Archival pigment print mounted to Dibond
Editioned at 43x62” / 32x46” / 24x34”

This is the last week to check out my exhibition in Seattle at Foster/White Gallery (@fosterwhitegallery). Let me know if you’d like a personal tour of the work if you’re in town and would like a respite from the smoke.

node.text:
Island 1, Hawai'i, 2011
Archival pigment print mounted to Dibond
Editioned at 50x62” / 38x46” / 28x34”

Excited to announce that I’m now represented by @fosterwhitegallery in Seattle! We’re currently preparing for the first showing of selected work from my ongoing series “Eons” alongside the incredible work of @david_burdeny from August 2nd to the 25th. Come say hello at the opening! Also, for print acquisition inquiries, please contact the gallery at seattle@fosterwhite.com

#imaginarymagnitude

Co-Existe (w/ @willett and @ezepini)
-
Thank you to @theoneclubforcreativity for naming this project in addition to ‘West’ as finalists in the upcoming #ADCAwards
I’m incredibly honored to be included with such exceptional talent in PDN’s 30 for 2018. Thank you so much, @pdnonline! Check out everyone’s work at www.pdns30.com

Black Canyon
#imaginarymagnitude -
Thank you to @candelafineart for the beautiful drum scans. It’s nice to know my negatives have graced the same surface as the film of @toddhido. Working on something big with these, more info in the coming weeks.

Andreaen Sand Dunes
#imaginarymagnitude
—
Recently chatted with @farmboyfinearts and @thepluspaper about my photography. Thanks for sharing my work and thoughts! Check out their pages for more info.

Occipital Lobe
#imaginarymagnitude -
Thank you to @booooooom for including my work in their annual 64 by 64! Check it out for an incredible collection of photography. Also, thank you to everyone who has supported my work and to those who have inspired me in 2017. 💚

Several Shades
--
An enormous thank you to the organizers and jurors of @photolucida Critical Mass. It's an honor to be included amongst so much talent in the Top 50 for 2017. 
I'm also excited to share the news that my work will be appearing at the Black Eye Gallery for Contemporary Photography in Sydney (@blackeyegallery) from October 30 to November 13th as a part of the "Ambient Landscapes" show. Huge thank you to @featureshoot!

And thank you to @booooooom for featuring some of my most recent work and to all of you helping to support my work!

#imaginarymagnitude

Caddo Lake
-
Thanks for the drum scan, @candelafineart. Excited to print this one.

Island, 2011
-
I recently chatted with @chromamagazine about photography and loneliness. Check out their Red Issue featuring interviews with artists including @shadowontherun, @alexwallbaum, @aleia and @brianvu.

Fire Season II
--
Enormously grateful to @pdnonline @rfwppi and @canonusa for including me in the Fall 2017 issue of Emerging Photographer. Link to the online issue at twitter.com/codycobb

Masking
--
I'm excited and honored to help judge the landscape photography competition for The Independent Photographer (@theindependentphoto) this month. Visit independent-photo.com before March 31st for more details.
